rComments: Great content -- lectures were always interesting!

Extremely tough marker and unclear with her grading rubric. She expects perfection with her papers. Her lectures don't relate to the content. She isn't subtle about who didn't do well and who did. But the topics are interesting.

Milne's exams are tough and she assigns quite a bit to read over the semester. She does go over material well though, and she makes an effort to be available to students if they don't understand. While her class isn't easy and the subject material was dry sometimes, she does care a lot about her students. She's tough but fair as a professor.

Overall the class was interesting at times. Despite the class discussing literary history, professor Milne only touches upon areas that are her focus of study rather than a general survey of literary history. She quickly develops favoritism for certain students early on in the semester. Her attitude was sarcastic, though she was witty at times.

Boring, unclear lecture. She doesn't explain what she expects on the exam or assignments well. For one assignment she called out people BY NAME to tell them they failed in front of everyone. Called out people for leaving lecture early and doesn't give breaks for a 2 hr class (besides making you dance)
Prof Milne is passionate about her teaching and has a wonderful ability to bring out the best in all of her students.  One of the best profs at U of T.
Boring lecturer, not very clear at all. Probably one of the least interesting classes I've ever taken. Dropped another class later because she was teaching it.
Prof is extremely rude. Hardly answers e-mails, and if she does it's usually "I can't help you with that". Very unclear on the structure of quizzes and the final exam. Condescending tone to students.
Gives a bunch of quizzes where the criteria is unclear, not a great lecturer and expects too much class participation. Tutorials are discussion based and not helpful.  Go to class.

rComments: Great prof, easy to talk to and very understanding. her assignments are fun, interesting and relevant.
Not a great teacher. She does not go in depth or teach anything beyond the obvious. Not very helpful outside of class either. Often gives confusing instructions on finals.

Horrid professor. She says everything thing she teaches is on her slides, which it isn't. Furthermore she never clearly explains her expectations for assignments then marks on criteria she did not specify in her outline.
